# Rutsubo — Contrato C-1: colección ejecutable de los 12 endpoints.
# Documentación viva (DoD): usable con el plugin REST Client de VS Code,
# IntelliJ HTTP Client o como referencia curl.
#
# Variables: arranca el daemon (`just dev`) y copia el token:
#   cat ~/.local/share/rutsubo/token

@base = http://127.0.0.1:7431
@token = PEGA_AQUI_EL_TOKEN
@session_id = PEGA_AQUI_UN_SESSION_ID
@approval_id = PEGA_AQUI_UN_APPROVAL_ID

### 1 · GET /v1/health — estado del daemon (único endpoint sin auth)
GET {{base}}/v1/health

### (control) cualquier otra ruta sin token responde 401 unauthorized
GET {{base}}/v1/sessions

### 2 · GET /v1/sessions — listar (paginado por cursor, filtro por estado)
GET {{base}}/v1/sessions?limit=20
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 2b · filtro por estado
GET {{base}}/v1/sessions?state=idle
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 3 · POST /v1/sessions — crear sesión sobre un workspace (201 + Location)
# workspace_path: absoluta, existente, sin traversal (RNF-05) → si no, 422
POST {{base}}/v1/sessions
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "workspace_path": "/home/ramses/MaestriaCyT/TPCA/Rutsubo",
  "title": "Sesión de prueba"
}

### 4 · GET /v1/sessions/{id} — detalle con contadores
GET {{base}}/v1/sessions/{{session_id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 5 · PATCH /v1/sessions/{id} — renombrar
PATCH {{base}}/v1/sessions/{{session_id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "title": "Refactor validación" }

### 5b · PATCH /v1/sessions/{id} — archivar (único cambio de estado permitido)
PATCH {{base}}/v1/sessions/{{session_id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "state": "archived" }

### 6 · POST /v1/sessions/{id}/messages — 202 siempre; idempotente por
#     client_msg_id (repetir la petición devuelve el mismo message_id);
#     409 session_busy si la sesión está en waiting_approval
POST {{base}}/v1/sessions/{{session_id}}/messages
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "content": "Revisa main.rs y corre los test",
  "client_msg_id": "11111111-2222-4333-8444-555555555555"
}

### 7 · GET /v1/sessions/{id}/events — replay (ascendente, limit máx 1000)
GET {{base}}/v1/sessions/{{session_id}}/events?after_seq=0&limit=100
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 8 · GET /v1/approvals — pendientes de todas las sesiones, antiguas primero
GET {{base}}/v1/approvals
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 9 · POST /v1/approvals/{id}/decision — la primera decisión gana; repetir
#     la misma → 200 con el registro original; la contraria → 409 conflict
POST {{base}}/v1/approvals/{{approval_id}}/decision
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "decision": "approve",
  "reason": "ok, es el módulo correcto",
  "remember_rule": false
}

### 10 · GET /v1/rules — reglas de auto-aprobación (RF-18)
GET {{base}}/v1/rules
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 10b · PUT /v1/rules — reemplazo completo del conjunto
PUT {{base}}/v1/rules
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "rules": [
    { "workspace_path": "/home/ramses/proyectos/demo", "tool": "run_shell", "pattern": "cargo test" }
  ]
}

### 11 · GET /v1/config/model — proveedores Groq del adapter LLM
GET {{base}}/v1/config/model
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 11b · PUT /v1/config/model — reemplazo completo (sin PATCH); aplica a
#      partir de la siguiente llamada; sin GROQ_API_KEY → 422
PUT {{base}}/v1/config/model
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "primary": { "provider": "groq", "model": "qwen/qwen3.6-27b" },
  "fallback": { "provider": "groq", "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b" },
  "thresholds": { "ttft_threshold_ms": 5000, "failure_window": 3, "cooldown_s": 60 }
}

### 12 · GET /v1/audit — paginado, filtros por sesión y proveedor (RF-22)
GET {{base}}/v1/audit?limit=25
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 12b · filtro por proveedor
GET {{base}}/v1/audit?provider=local:mock:qwen3.5-8b
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 13 · POST /v1/asr/transcribe — audio multipart (máximo 25 MB)
POST {{base}}/v1/asr/transcribe
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=RutsuboBoundary

--RutsuboBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="audio"; filename="sample.webm"
Content-Type: audio/webm

< ./sample.webm
--RutsuboBoundary--

### 14 · POST /v1/ws/ticket — ticket efímero (60 s, un solo uso) para el
#      handshake del WS cuando no se puede mandar Authorization (navegador
#      remoto). Conectar luego con ws(s)://…/v1/ws?ticket=<ticket>
POST {{base}}/v1/ws/ticket
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

# WebSocket (Fase D, contrato C-3): no es HTTP plano, se prueba con wscat:
#   npx wscat -c "ws://127.0.0.1:7431/v1/ws?token=$(cat ~/.local/share/rutsubo/token)"
#   > {"v":1,"type":"subscribe_session","payload":{"session_id":"…","after_seq":0},"session_id":"…","ts":"2026-07-09T18:00:00Z"}
